<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 30 at 5:56PM CDT  by NWS Springfield</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Bourbon
and northern Crawford Counties through 630 PM CDT...
At 553 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
St. Paul, moving northeast at 60 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Fort Scott, Girard, Marmaton, Walnut, Hepler, Hiattville, Farlington,
Brazilton, Greenbush, Garland and Pawnee Station.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
